JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department is refuting a study on school placement problems. The Centre for Child Law says the department is to blame for ongoing issues since 2015 including not placing pupils from other provinces quickly enough. READ: Online placement process complete: Lesufi The department responded that every year brings new challenges that place it under huge pressure. Departmental spokesperson Steve Mabona said the research obtained from a distance without interacting with the department is disingenuous and unfair. READ: Not enough classrooms for Gauteng pupils: expert Mabona said outstanding placements in the area were mainly drawn from disputed cases and inner grades, like Grade 10 and 11.